# Project Overview
This project is a three‑page responsive website built for my Level 2 Final Integrated Project (FIP). The goal is to create a modern rebrand of Swerve, a fictional beverage company, using clean, semantic HTML, organized CSS, and interactive JavaScript components.

The website includes:

- A Home Page (index.html)

- A Products Page (products.html)

- A Contact Page (contact.html) with a fully functional form

All pages follow a consistent grid system, typography scale, and brand styling inspired by the Swerve rebrand concept.


## Project Requirements (as assigned)
Build three fully functional web pages

One page must be index.html

One page must include a contact form

Must use HTML, CSS, and JavaScript

Must demonstrate:

Responsive layout

Interactive elements

Clean code structure

Visual consistency across pages


## Technical Implementation
### HTML
Semantic structure for accessibility and clarity

Reusable components (navigation, footer, cards, sections)

Grid-based layout using a custom grid.css system

Contact form with labeled inputs and textarea

### CSS
Custom grid system for desktop, tablet, and mobile

Card components with borders, shadows, and spacing

Responsive product grid

Hero sections with image/text alignment

Circular staff cards

Overlay button (“How It Started”) using absolute positioning

Mobile-first breakpoints for all major sections

### JavaScript
FAQ accordion with:

Smooth open/close animation

Fade‑in content

Rotating + icon

One‑open‑at‑a‑time behavior

Optional enhancements:

Scroll animations

Hover interactions

Form validation


